title: Cumberbatch Sihns Pro Deal
text:
Talk about it in NJHoops Hardwood Talk St. Bonaventure graduate Andell Cumberbatch has signed a professional contract to play for MMCITE Brno of the Kooperativa National Basketball League in the Czech Republic. The 6-foot-5, 190-lb. Cumberbatch was a two-year starter for the Bonnies at small forward from 2013-15. Last season as a senior, he averaged 10.1 points, 4.9 rebounds and 1.9 assists per game. Cumberbatch made 36 percent (38-105) of his three-point attempts. He also was widely regarded for his defensive work, routinely assigned to guard the opponent's best offensive player.Cumberbatch helped the Bonnies win 18 games in each of his two seasons. Cumberbatch, who earned a degree in international studies from St. Bonaventure, is the 17th St. Bonaventure men's basketball alumnus to sign a professional contract since Mark Schmidt became the Bonnies' head coach in 2007. Cumberbatch was a 21011 graduate of East Orange.NJ Hoops provides blanket coverage of NJ basketball all year long for the past 20 years and is proud to continue to be the NJ nominating source for the McDonald's All American game
